HEADWORD: Coping
<hw>Cop"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Cope</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The highest or covering
course of masonry in a wall, often with sloping edges to carry off
water; -- sometimes called <altname>capping</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Gwill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
